[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms:
- resolve
- route
- escalate
- complete
contract:
  input:
    verdict: string
    confidence: number
    reason: string
    goal: object
  output:
    resolution: string
    cns_spans: array
    escalate_to_human: boolean
    escalate_reason: string
energy_cap: 2048
visibility: Public
---
{# Template: goal-analysis/goal-resolve.j2 #}
{# goal: Route goal verdict to resolution action and emit appropriate CNS spans. #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "low"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 512
thinking_budget = "off"

Resolve the goal based on the judge's verdict. Low confidence (&lt; 0.7) escalates to human regardless of verdict.

Input:
```json
{
  "verdict": "{{ verdict }}",
  "confidence": {{ confidence }},
  "reason": "{{ reason }}",
  "goal": {{ goal | tojson }}
}
```

Resolution rules:
- verdict "done" + confidence >= 0.7 → complete (emit reg.goal.complete)
- verdict "done" + confidence &lt; 0.7 → escalate to human (emit reg.goal.alert.escalate)
- verdict "continue" → continue loop (emit reg.goal.transition)
- verdict "blocked" → escalate to human (emit reg.goal.block)
- Any verdict with confidence &lt; 0.7 → escalate (low confidence may still be wrong)

Emit appropriate CNS spans based on resolution:
- complete → ["reg.goal.verify", "reg.goal.complete"]
- continue → ["reg.goal.verify", "reg.goal.transition"]
- escalate (blocked) → ["reg.goal.verify", "reg.goal.block", "reg.goal.alert.escalate"]
- escalate (low confidence) → ["reg.goal.verify", "reg.goal.alert.escalate"]

Return JSON only — select the correct cns_spans for the resolution:
```json
{
  "resolution": "complete",
  "cns_spans": ["reg.goal.verify", "reg.goal.complete"],
  "escalate_to_human": false,
  "escalate_reason": ""
}
```
